20. quod: a rare example from the Augustan age of the use of quod with subj. for acc. and inf. But the passages which Breiter cites in support of it, Man. iv. 250 and Verg. Aen. ix. 289 (where quod depends on linquo not on teslis; Madvig Op. 290), are obviously not parallel. An ante-Augustan parallel would be Plaut. Asin. 52 scio iam filius quod amet meus.
